The GM RSA was modelled according to the neutral theory of ecosystems proposed by [22]. Here, the dynamics of the population of a single species are governed by generalized birth and death events, that include speciation, immigration and emigration. If we neglect inter-species interactions after the community has reached a steady state, the number of individuals n of a given species evolves according to equation 
